StressCategory.createLoop(int) calls method on LoggerRepository Interface 
which doesn't exist. It is improperly assuming that the LoggerRepository 
returned is of type Hierarchy which does have a .clear() method.

Either LoggerRepository needs to be modified so all implementors of this 
interface offer a .clear() method signature or the following code changes in 
StressCategory.createLoop(int) should be modified.

Current(1.2rc1):
      // Clear hash table for next round
      LogManager.getLoggerRepository().clear();
Suggested change:
      // Clear hash table for next round
      if(LogManager.getLoggerRepository() instanceof Hierarchy)
      { LogManager.getLoggerRepository().clear(); }
